# Exchange Design System — Mandatory Prototype Rules

## Figma Sources (always reference first)
- **XDS Exchange Design System:** https://www.figma.com/design/S5vzHnfEkTU1uETKnVOl7x/XDS---Exchange-Design-System
- **Exchange Brand Playbook:** https://www.figma.com/slides/Oyb9M17fbUWZl4C7ZTO3jQ/Exchange-Brand-Playbook

## Rule 1 — Always import the design system
Every new prototype HTML file MUST import both CSS files at the top:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./design-system/tokens.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./design-system/components.css">
```

If the prototype is in a subdirectory, adjust the path accordingly (e.g. `../design-system/tokens.css`).

## Rule 2 — Use design tokens for all visual properties
Never hardcode colours, spacing, font sizes, border radii, or shadows. Always use `var(--xds-*)` tokens:

```css
/* ✅ Correct */
background: var(--xds-surface-elevated);
color: var(--xds-text-primary);
padding: var(--xds-space-12);
border-radius: var(--xds-radius-lg);
font-size: var(--xds-font-size-base);

/* ❌ Never do this */
background: #1A1A36;
color: white;
padding: 24px;
```

## Rule 3 — Dark theme by default
All Exchange prototypes use a dark theme. The page root must always be:

```css
body {
  background: var(--xds-surface-page);   /* #0D0D1C */
  color: var(--xds-text-primary);
}
```

Never use light backgrounds on Exchange surfaces.

## Rule 4 — Use component classes for standard elements
Use `.xds-*` classes for all standard UI components before writing custom CSS:

- Buttons: `.xds-btn .xds-btn-primary` / `.xds-btn-secondary` / `.xds-btn-ghost` / `.xds-btn-danger`
- Cards: `.xds-card`
- Inputs: `.xds-input`, `.xds-select`, `.xds-textarea`
- Status badges: `.xds-badge .xds-badge-active` / `.xds-badge-scheduled` / `.xds-badge-draft` / `.xds-badge-ended` / `.xds-badge-deactivated`
- Tables: `.xds-table`, `.xds-table-wrap`
- Tabs: `.xds-tabs`, `.xds-tab`
- Navigation: `.xds-nav`
- Info blocks: `.xds-info-block` (add `.success`, `.warning`, `.error`, `.purple` modifiers)
- Modals: `.xds-modal-overlay`, `.xds-modal`

## Rule 5 — Typography
Always use Inter font. Apply it via `var(--xds-font-family-base)`.
Use typographic utility classes for headings: `.xds-h1` through `.xds-h5`, `.xds-body`, `.xds-label`.

## Rule 6 — Spacing
Use the spacing scale exclusively. Never invent arbitrary pixel values:
`--xds-space-2 (4px)` → `--xds-space-4 (8px)` → `--xds-space-6 (12px)` → `--xds-space-8 (16px)` → `--xds-space-12 (24px)` → `--xds-space-16 (32px)`

## Rule 7 — Colour meaning
Respect semantic colour assignments:
- `--xds-color-brand-blue` → primary interactive / CTA only
- `--xds-color-brand-green` → positive values, gains, success states
- `--xds-color-brand-red` → negative values, losses, errors, destructive actions
- `--xds-color-brand-gold` → VIP, premium, rewards
- `--xds-color-brand-cyan` → data charts, highlights, accents

## Rule 8 — Status badges for campaign states
Always use the XDS badge classes for campaign lifecycle states:
- Draft → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-draft`
- Scheduled → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-scheduled`
- Active → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-active`
- Ended → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-ended`
- Deactivated → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-deactivated`

## Rule 9 — Navigation
All pages must have a top nav using `.xds-nav` with the Exchange brand icon and name.

## Rule 10 — When the design system doesn't cover something
If a component is not in the design system CSS files, check the Figma XDS file first before inventing a style. Build the new component using existing tokens. Never introduce new colour values, font sizes, or spacing values that don't come from the token scale.
